hopobject.body: I'm not interested in football letco medical australia After skyrocketing to fame on 'Britain's Got Talent,' Boyle seemed to crack under the pressure of being in the spotlight. Though she had wowed fans with her sensational voice and sold more than 8 million copies of her debut album, in 2009 the singer reportedly felt very scared and isolated. She ultimately canceled a series of performances and landed in the hospital to recover from the stress. Her brother Gerry later told People magazine, 'When the lights switch off and the audience goes home, Susan is very much on her own.'
